</li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-ctqQKy eJZCTA pf-48_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Types of innovation</strong></h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-cbTzjv cdRhtw pf-50_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hjGZqJ gtgMXo pf-51_ pf-text-1"><strong>Product innovation</strong> - Developing new or improved products.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hjGZqJ gtgMXo pf-53_ pf-text-1"><strong>Process innovation </strong>- Implementing new or significantly improved production or delivery methods.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hjGZqJ gtgMXo pf-55_ pf-text-1"><strong>Service innovation</strong> - Creating new or enhanced services.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hjGZqJ gtgMXo pf-57_ pf-text-1"><strong>Business model innovation</strong> - Developing new ways of doing business to create and capture value.



